          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2022-01-27 10:19:46" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(derivative of {L:οὐρανός&lt;SDBG:οὐρανός:000001&gt;}[b] heaven, {D:1.11}) related to or located in heaven</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>heavenly</Gloss>
                <Gloss>in heaven</Gloss>
                <Gloss>pertaining to heaven</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>The derivatives οὐράνιος and {L:ἐπουράνιος&lt;SDBG:ἐπουράνιος:000001&gt;}[b] are essentially equivalent to semantic compounds in that they combine a semantic element of heaven as a celestial abode with another semantic element specifying location or relationship. Frequently such terms are translated as ‘in heaven’ or ‘from heaven’ or ‘belonging to heaven.’</Comments>
